# Booking Flow

## 1. Overview

This is the flowchart for the booking process

**Full Flow**

![Booking Flow](/docs/bookingFlowFull.png)

**Search Flight**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Select Add-on Service**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Create Booking**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

This RESTful endpoint will allow users to add new reservations to the system. This request is subject to underlying permission checks and is not available to unauthenticated users.

```  
Endpoints: POST /reservations
```

Here is a sample of what a basic request would look like for a reservation with one passengers on a single leg of travel.

## 2. Booking steps

The following is a worked example of the steps required to book via the REST API.

**Step 1. Search flights**

**Step 2. Select flight**

The response of this request will contain many travel options. Select a flight

**Step 3. Select booking key**

Pick up the **booking key** can be retained to be used in the booking request

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Step 4. Building body request**

**4.1 Start building up a booking request by providing booking Information**

```json
    "bookingInformation": {
        "contactInformation": {
            "name": "OTA company",
            "phoneNumber": "hotline",
            "extension": "",
            "email": "huannguyen@vietjetair.com",
            "language": {
                "code": "en",
                "name": "English"
            }
        }
    }
```

**4.3. Building up a booking request by providing journey Information**

```json
    "journeys": [
        {
            "index": 1,
            "passengerJourneyDetails": [
                {
                    "passenger": {
                        "index": 1
                    },
                    "bookingKey": "{{booking_Key}}",
                    "reservationStatus": {
                        "confirmed": true,
                        "waitlist": false,
                        "standby": false,
                        "cancelled": false,
                        "open": false,
                        "finalized": false,
                        "external": false
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
```

Since this is the only one trip on the reservation, the index will be '1'. If there was return trip, it's index would be '2'.

```json
    "journeys": [
        {
            "index": 1,
            "passengerJourneyDetails": [
                {
                    "passenger": {
                        "index": 1
                    },
                    "segment": null,
                    "bookingKey": "{{booking_Key}}",
                    "reservationStatus": {
                        "confirmed": true,
                        "waitlist": false,
                        "standby": false,
                        "cancelled": false,
                        "open": false,
                        "finalized": false,
                        "external": false
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "index": 2,
            "passengerJourneyDetails": [
                {
                    "passenger": {
                        "index": 1
                    },
                    "segment": null,
                    "bookingKey": "{{booking_Key}}",
                    "reservationStatus": {
                        "confirmed": true,
                        "waitlist": false,
                        "standby": false,
                        "cancelled": false,
                        "open": false,
                        "finalized": false,
                        "external": false
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
```

This is the only passenger on the reservation, the index will be '1'. If there was another passenger, it's index would be '2', and so on.

The booking key pulled from the travel options response will be provided to the bookingKey portion of the request.

Next, add in the segment status information. For most use cases, the desired status will be 'confirmed'.

```json
    "reservationStatus": {
        "confirmed": true,
        "waitlist": false,
        "standby": false,
        "cancelled": false,
        "open": false,
        "finalized": false,
        "external": false
    }
```

**4.4 Add the reservation status.**

This status applies to the reservation journey as a whole and is independent from the individual segment statuses.

```json
    "reservationStatus": {
        "cancelled": false,
        "open": false,
        "finalized": false,
        "external": false
    } 
```

**4.8.1 Get payment method by booking**

Retrieves a list of the payment method. This will return all valid payment methods for the provided booking key.The lists of payment methods for each journey would then be amalgamated presenting only payment methods valid for all journeys on the reservation to user at the end of the booking process

- Select the **identifier** and **key** will need to be retained for use in the payment portion of the booking request

**Step 5. The next step is to retrieve a price quotation.**

This is achieved using the Quotations endpoint. The reservation body request information is passed into the request body of the Quotations request as it will appear on the reservation. The Quotations endpoint will then calculate and return all relevant charges. In this case, the above request will be supplied to the Quotations endpoint which will return a list of all charges that need to be applied to the reservation.

_The total cost can now be added to the booking request under currencyAmounts.totalAmount. The total processing fee can now be added to the booking request under processing CurrencyAmounts. totalAmount._

**Step 6. The request is now ready to be submitted.**

If it is successfully completed the server should respond with an HTTP 200 and reservation response.

**Step 7: Sent email itinerary**

After the payment booking, requirement to send email itinerary to customer
